        <p class="lead">
          We have audited hundreds of websites from businesses across Ahmedabad, from textile exporters in Maninagar to real estate developers near SG Highway. The same SEO problems show up repeatedly. Some of them are quick fixes. Others require rethinking an entire approach. All of them are costing local businesses real money in missed leads every single month.
        </p>

        <p>
          Here are the 10 SEO mistakes we see most often, along with exactly what to do about each one.
        </p>

        <h2 id="ahmedabad-seo-different">Why Ranking in Ahmedabad Takes a Different Approach</h2>
        <p>
          Google's algorithm weighs local signals very differently from national ones. When someone in Vastrapur searches "interior designer near me," Google looks at your proximity, your Google Business Profile completeness, your reviews, and your on-page local signals before it even considers backlinks or domain age. Most businesses chase national SEO tactics while ignoring the local foundations that actually drive calls from customers in their city.
        </p>
        <p>
          That is the gap we see over and over. Let us close it.
        </p>

        <h2 id="mistake-1-gbp">Mistake 1: Treating Your Google Business Profile as an Afterthought</h2>
        <p>
          Your Google Business Profile (GBP) is more important than your own website for local searches. If it is incomplete, has wrong hours, or has no photos, Google deprioritises you regardless of how well-built your website is.
        </p>
        <p>
          We have seen businesses with professionally designed websites ranking below competitors who had nothing but a fully filled-out GBP. Categories, photos, service areas, Q&amp;A responses, regular posts, and review replies all factor into where you appear.
        </p>
        <h3 id="fix-gbp">What to do instead</h3>
        <p>
          Fill in every field: primary and secondary categories, opening hours (including public holidays), a business description with your main service and city name, at least 15 photos, and a reply to every review. Add a Google Post at least twice a month. Enable messaging and respond within a few hours. This single change has moved clients from page 3 to page 1 in Ahmedabad local results within 60 days.
        </p>

        <h2 id="mistake-2-keywords">Mistake 2: Targeting Keywords That No One in Gujarat Searches</h2>
        <p>
          Ranking for "digital marketing agency" is extremely competitive and largely useless if your clients are in Ahmedabad. Meanwhile, "digital marketing agency Ahmedabad" or "SEO company Satellite Ahmedabad" has much lower competition and much higher purchase intent from people who will actually contact you.
        </p>
        <h3 id="fix-keywords">How to find the right local keywords</h3>
        <p>
          Open Google in a private browsing window with your location set to Ahmedabad. Type your main service and watch the autocomplete suggestions. Those are real searches. Also check the "People also ask" box in results and the "Related searches" at the bottom of the page. Google Search Console will show you the exact queries already bringing people to your site, and that list usually has opportunities you are not fully ranking for yet.
        </p>

        <h2 id="mistake-3-location-pages">Mistake 3: Running One Website When You Need Location Pages</h2>
        <p>
          If you serve multiple areas such as Ahmedabad, Gandhinagar, and Surat, one homepage with "We serve all of Gujarat" in the footer does not tell Google anything useful. Location-specific pages with genuine content about each market rank far better for area-specific searches than a single generic page.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each location page needs its own title tag, meta description, H1, at least 600 words of real content about that market, references to specific neighborhoods or business areas, and a Google Maps embed confirming your presence there.
        </p>

        <h2 id="mistake-4-reviews">Mistake 4: Having Zero Strategy for Google Reviews</h2>
        <p>
          Reviews directly influence local pack rankings. Businesses with 50+ reviews that include recent activity consistently outrank businesses with 10 reviews that stopped getting new ones two years ago. The mistake is not asking for reviews at all, or asking in ways that feel awkward and get ignored.
        </p>
        <p>
          Build a simple review process: after completing a project, send the client a direct link to your Google review page via WhatsApp. Follow up once if you do not hear back in a week. Respond to every review, including critical ones, within 24 hours. Consistency matters far more than a one-time push to gather 50 reviews overnight.
        </p>

        <h2 id="mistake-5-speed">Mistake 5: Letting Website Speed Drain Your Rankings</h2>
        <p>
          Core Web Vitals are a confirmed Google ranking factor. A website that takes 6 seconds to load on a mobile connection is losing leads and rankings at the same time. We regularly audit Ahmedabad business websites and find uncompressed images at 3 to 4 MB each, render-blocking scripts from third-party tools, and no server-side caching in place. All of these are fixable.
        </p>
        <p>
          Run your site through Google PageSpeed Insights today. A score below 50 on mobile is urgent. Fix it before spending another rupee on Google Ads or content creation, because slow speed reduces the impact of everything else you do.
        </p>


        <!-- MID-ARTICLE CTA -->
        <div class="mid-cta">
          <div class="mid-cta-inner">
            <span class="mid-cta-tag">Free SEO Audit</span>
            <h3>Find Out Exactly What Is Hurting Your Rankings</h3>
