            <a href="/free-seo-audit" class="btn btn-white">Get My Free SEO Audit</a>
          </div>
        </div>


        <h2 id="mistake-6-content">Mistake 6: Publishing Thin Content That Says Nothing Specific</h2>
        <p>
          "We are a leading web design company offering best-in-class solutions" tells Google nothing and tells your potential customers nothing either. Google rewards content that genuinely answers the questions people search for. If you sell packaging solutions in GIDC Vatva, write about the specific packaging challenges manufacturers in that industrial area face. That level of specificity is what ranks.
        </p>
        <p>
          Aim for a minimum of 800 words on service pages and 1,200 words on location pages. Use real examples, specific numbers where you have them, and local references that confirm you actually operate in Ahmedabad and understand its business environment.
        </p>

        <h2 id="mistake-7-mobile">Mistake 7: Building a Desktop Site and Hoping Mobile Works</h2>
        <p>
          Google indexes the mobile version of your website first. If your mobile experience has tiny text, buttons packed too closely together, or a navigation menu that does not work on touchscreens, you are being penalised for it. In Ahmedabad, where the large majority of searches happen on Android phones, this is a critical error.
        </p>
        <p>
          Test your site on an actual Android device, not just a browser emulator. Is the phone number in your header a clickable link? Does your contact form work without needing to zoom in? Does the menu close properly after selecting a page? These small details matter for both rankings and conversions.
        </p>

        <h2 id="mistake-8-schema">Mistake 8: Skipping Local Schema Markup Entirely</h2>
        <p>
          Schema markup is structured code that tells Google precisely what your page is about. LocalBusiness schema communicates your business name, address, phone number, opening hours, and service area in a format that Google can read with confidence. Most Ahmedabad business websites have none of this.
        </p>
        <p>
          At minimum, add LocalBusiness schema to your homepage with your complete NAP (name, address, phone), your business category, your opening hours, and your service area. Service pages should have Service schema. FAQ sections should have FAQPage schema. None of this requires advanced technical knowledge.
        </p>

        <h2 id="mistake-9-internal-links">Mistake 9: Treating Every Page as an Island</h2>
        <p>
          Internal links distribute ranking authority across your site and help Google understand which pages are most important. Businesses that publish 20 blog posts and never link between them or back to their service pages are wasting a free, powerful ranking signal.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every new piece of content you publish should link to at least two other pages on your site, ideally including a relevant service page or location page. Your service pages should link to related blog posts. Think of it as building an interconnected web of content rather than a flat list of separate pages.
        </p>

        <h2 id="mistake-10-audits">Mistake 10: Running Blind Without Regular SEO Audits</h2>
        <p>
          Google updates its algorithm hundreds of times per year. A site that ranked well 18 months ago may have been knocked down by a core update since then. Without regular audits using tools like Google Search Console, Ahrefs, or Semrush, you would not even know until your phone stops ringing.
        </p>
        <p>
          Run a basic technical audit every quarter. Check for broken links, crawl errors, and pages that have dropped in impressions. Every month, open Search Console and look at which queries are gaining or losing clicks. This takes about 30 minutes and catches problems before they become serious.
        </p>

        <h2 id="bottom-line">The Bottom Line</h2>
        <p>
          None of these 10 mistakes require a large budget to fix. Most require time, attention, and consistency rather than money. If you address even five of the items on this list, you will likely see a measurable improvement in local rankings within 90 days.
        </p>
        <p>
          The businesses ranking at the top of Ahmedabad search results right now are not there by luck. They filled out their Google Business Profile completely. They wrote real content about specific services in specific locations. They made sure their site loads quickly on a phone. They built a process for gathering reviews. And they kept doing these things while competitors did not.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you want a clear picture of exactly which of these issues affect your specific website, our team offers a free SEO audit for Gujarat businesses. You get a detailed review of your site, your GBP, and your current keyword positions, with a prioritised list of fixes to work through. No sales call required.
        </p>

